Subject: [Caml-list] [ANN] Uutf 0.9.3 & Xmlm 1.2.0

Hello,=20=20

I'd like to announce the release of Uutf 0.9.3 and Xmlm 1.2.0, see below fo=
r details. They should soon be available in opam.=20=20

Best,

Daniel


* Uutf 0.9.3

Bugfix release (thanks to Edwin T=C3=B6r=C3=B6k for the report), see the re=
lease notes for details.

Home page: http://erratique.ch/software/uutf
Release notes: https://github.com/dbuenzli/uutf/blob/master/CHANGES.md


* Xmlm 1.2.0=20=20

Minor release that improves the odds of generating well-formed XML by autom=
atically translating illegal XML unicode characters present in output `Data=
 signals or attributes to the unicode replacement character U+FFFD (thanks =
to David Sheets for insisting that something should be done about that). It=
 also deprecates the following two features:

1) The (non-standard) ability to decode more than one document with the sam=
e input abstraction.
See http://erratique.ch/software/xmlm/doc/Xmlm#iseq

2) The functorial interface that allows to specify alternative datatypes fo=
r strings and internal buffers.=20=20
See http://erratique.ch/software/xmlm/doc/Xmlm#sto

Please get in touch if 1) or 2) is important/affects you.

For other changes consult the release notes.

Home page: http://erratique.ch/software/xmlm
Release notes: https://github.com/dbuenzli/xmlm/blob/master/CHANGES.md




